title: For Sale:  VG6 Precison CAGE Device Concussion Altering Gas Expansion
postcontent: Muzzle Brake Attachement System for Enhancing Performance The CAGE is the pinnacle of concussion reduction technology. Its primary essential task was to disrupt side concussion while keeping or enhancing the characteristics of the Gamma and Epsilon series of muzzle devices. It accomplishes this with ease. The CAGE does not use a large tubular construction because gas dynamics used for muzzle brakes do not operate efficiently when transferring energy into them. Instead it features a close wrap fit. This allows the CAGE to distribute the gases in a manner conducive to both muzzle control and concussion disruption. The sides of the CAGE utilize a series/pattern of small holes which move over the chambers of the Gamma and Epsilon devices. This allows the gasses to expend energy more uniformly and slows them down while moving through the porting thus disrupting horizontal concussion AND allowing the muzzle brake to have more time to influence the gaseous escape through all the ports. This leads to an extremely smooth recoil and zero muzzle flip by “bleeding off energy” rather than abruptly losing energy. The CAGE device offers absolute control while sparing the concussion of a bare muzzle brake.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Deluxe 1892 Full Fancy LETTER NICE 1903
postcontent: Great and RARE ORIGINAL 1892 Winchester FULL FANCY DELUXE octagon Rifle in 25-20 WCF. Serial Number is 166683 and the date of manufacture is 1903. This fine Winchester includes its Cody Museum research sheet and Letters up PERFECTLY. Any original 1892 Full Deluxe with factory H checkering and Fancy wood is a rare find. The extra factory features of set triggers and takedown make this example about as rare as it gets in 1892 collecting. The condition is very nice and all original. There are NO extra holes or other non-factory alterations. The original blue is strong and bright (not brown) with some small areas of spotting on the receiver and barrel. Strong original case color remains on the lever. The screws, mechanics and bore are all excellent. We rate the bore at near mint, probably a 9.5 out of 10. The takedown is tight and this rifle shows signs that is was fired and used very little over the years. The stock and forend are in excellent original shape and look to never have been removed from the rifle. The original factory H checkering is strong and the wood to metal fit is outstanding everywhere. If you collect Deluxe Winchester Rifles, you don't want to miss out on this one as it has rarity, condition , originality and beauty. We only see about one original 1892 Full Fancy Deluxe about every 2 years and this is the first with the original set triggers.

title: For Sale/Trade:  GAMEKING
postcontent: The Nikko Stirling GameKing 3.5-10x44 LRX Illuminated Riflescopes have a variable zoom magnification allowing hunters greater flexibility in their hunting. You can simply adjust the zoom according to the conditions as you move through the hunting terrain. When the forest is thickest and the game is closer you can easily move the zoom to the lowest setting. This has the result of increasing your field of view so that the target can easily be seen without delay. Later when you move to more open fields the quick adjustment of the zoom will allow accurate shots on the furthest targets. Suitable for optical clarity enhancement allowing you greater contrast in the field. Coatings designed to reduce the reflection of light as it passes through your riflescope to your eye. Parallax and fine focus are critical on riflescopes used to hunt game over a large range of distances. Under the watertight adjustment caps you find accurate finger adjustable bezels for quickly adjusting the windage and elevation in your scope. All illuminated scopes have glass reticle. Glass etched Mil Dot reticles provide crisp illumination without glare that can blind the hunter in low light. The illumination is easily adjusted for brightness allowing use in daylight or twilight. Actual magnification is 3.5-10. Objective diameter is 44 millimeters. Field of view at 100 yards is 38-12.67. Eye relief is 3.25 Inch.
